social_posts.post_text: Three years ago today! This still goes down as a bucket list sighting, and one of the most unusual. While the mountain lion was wild, the setting was anything but. This was taken from a gas station parking lot in town, surrounded by other photographers and bystanders. That said, it was still an incredible sight to witness and I count myself lucky to have seen this beautiful lady in action!
"We must walk on in the days ahead with an audacious faith in the future.” — Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.

social_posts.post_text: When the temperatures drop below zero we got some of the most beautiful conditions—including these layers of low lying fog. When the first rays of the day hit them they burn off in beautiful swirls and wisps.
A meeting of the minds for international moose day!

34 turns around the sun! I don’t have any birthday blues today, but couldn’t resist sharing this blue hour shot. Birthdays are the perfect time for taking stock and reflecting. As always I’m so grateful to call this incredible place home. 💙

We just got our FULL WEDDING GALLERY and I am so in love! It’s incredible to get to relive the best day through these photos. Please indulge me while we take a brief break from your regularly scheduled wildlife and mountain content to go on a little journey through our wedding day! Starting with PART ONE: getting ready and first looks 💕

PC: @nicoleastonphoto

PART TWO of the best day: the ceremony. Rain had threatened all day and right before I walked down the aisle it briefly sprinkled before relenting just in time. David and I have been together for over eight years so this moment was a long time coming and well worth the wait. 🤍

(Please indulge me while we take a brief break from your regularly scheduled wildlife and mountain content to go on a little journey through our wedding day as we just got our full gallery and I’m obsessed!) PC: @nicoleastonphoto

PART THREE of the best day: the reception. Working in the wedding industry myself, I actually loved planning our wedding and selecting all of the details. Seeing it all come together in real life was a dream come true! One of my favorite details was the books—instead of table numbers each table was identified by a love story.

(If you missed my previous disclaimer, please indulge me while we take a brief break from your regularly scheduled wildlife and mountain content to go on a little journey through our wedding day as we just got our full gallery and I’m obsessed!) PC: @nicoleastonphoto

PART FOUR of the best day: the party. So. Much. Joy. These photos bring an enormous smile to my face! It was an absolute blast to dance and celebrate with family and friends. There was a time in my life when I thought that I could never be life of the party without alcohol, I’d say these photos are stunning proof to the contrary! We had the traditional signature drinks (named after our cats), beer, wine, etc, AND and we had a soda bar with syrups and fixings for the nondrinkers in the crowd like myself. So yes, that enormous smile you see is powered by joy, love, and a little Dr. Pepper. 💕

(Thanks for indulging me while we took a brief break from your regularly scheduled wildlife and mountain content to go on a little journey through our wedding day, that’s a wrap!) PC: @nicoleastonphoto
